[3] Indonesia (Central Java)
Date: Wed 25 Jun 2008
Source: Sura Merdeka CyberNews (in Indonesian, machine translated, edited]
<http://www.suaramerdeka.com/beta1/index.php?fuseaction=news.detailNews&id_news=8532>


Dengue fever in the lower parts of Central Java is endemic, and the
number of patients is increasing. This report mentions a doubling of
the number of dengue patients in Central Java in 2007 compared to
2006. In 2006, deaths resulting from dengue reached 220, and the
figure increased in 2007 to 329 people.

According to Dr. Dwi Heri of the Health Authority, in examining the
dengue case data, the disease is spreading in various areas. The
dangerous illness increased not only in the number of sufferers but
also in the number of deaths.

The number of sufferers also increased from 10 924 in 2006 to 20 565
sufferers in 2007.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

