[4] Viet Nam
Date: Wed 25 Jun 2008
Source: VietNamNet Bridge [edited]
<http://english.vietnamnet.vn/social/2008/06/790360/>


The Ministry of Health on [24 Jun 2008] continued warning of the
spread of dengue fever in southern provinces.

The past week witnessed a report of over 1400 dengue fever patients
in 27 locations, 4 of whom died, raising the total number of cases to
19 859 so far this year [2008], including 20 deaths.

Provinces with the highest numbers of patients are Ho Chi Minh City
3754 cases/2 dead, Soc Trang 1717 cases/1 dead, Tien Giang 1489
cases/1 dead, and Ca Mau 1123 cases/3 dead. Hanoi has had nearly 100
cases.

The Health Ministry noted that though the total number of patients is
less than last year's [2007] figure, the disease could spread even
more widely as the rainy season has come.

[Byline: L. Ha]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MBDS <promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[A total of 19 859 dengue cases and 20 deaths have been reported in
Viet Nam in 2008. There were 12 064 dengue cases with 11 fatalities
reported in an earlier posting 2 weeks ago, on 11 Jun 2008 (see prior
PRO/MBDS posting Dengue - Viet Nam (05) 20080612.1865).

According to the newswire above, while the number of cases of dengue
reported to date this year (2008) is approximately the same as the
number of cases of dengue reported during the same time frame last
year (2007), there were more than twice the number of deaths
attributable to dengue in this period in 2007. There were almost 20
000 cases and 21 deaths of dengue fever detected by 22 Jun 2007 (see
prior PRO/MBDS posting Dengue - Viet Nam (07) 20070622.2025).

For maps of Viet Nam with provinces, see
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_admin01.jpg> and
<http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Viet Nam can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=14.9,108.5,5>.
This map shows other outbreaks in Viet Nam and surrounding countries
that have been reported on ProMED-mail. The postings can be directly
accessed through this map. - Mods.YMA/MPP]

