[6] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Wed 25 Jun 2008
Source: JC Online [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://jc.uol.com.br/2008/06/25/not_172397.php>


The state Secretariat of Health of Rio de Janeiro reported the total
number of dengue cases and deaths in the state this year [2008];
according to the data, there were 142 confirmed dengue deaths, the
majority of which occurred between January and April 2008, when there
was an outbreak of the disease. Another 130 cases are under
investigation. The majority of the cases (82) occurred in the city of
Rio de Janeiro. Other municipalities which registered a large number
of dengue deaths were Duque de Caxias (19 cases) [a town bordering the
city of Rio. - Mod.JW] and Angra dos Reis (10 cases).

One in every 3 dengue deaths were in children and youths of 0 to 15
years of age. The registered total cases of the disease [in the state
in 2008] were 195 000, the majority (102 000) in the municipalities of
Rio de Janeiro, Nova Iguacu (15 000), Angra dos Reis (11 000) and
Campos (9700).

--
